9,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/3/5/b899/\",\"body_value\":\"“If someone takes to Kṛṣṇa consciousness, even though he may not follow the prescribed duties in the \u003cem\u003eśāstras\u003c/em\u003e or execute the devotional service properly, and even though he may fall down from the standard, there is no loss or evil for him. But if he carries out all the injunctions for purification in the \u003cem\u003eśāstras,\u003c/em\u003e what does it avail him if he is not Kṛṣṇa conscious?” So the purificatory process is necessary for reaching this point of Kṛṣṇa consciousness. Therefore, \u003cem\u003esannyāsa,\u003c/em\u003e or any purificatory process, is to help reach the ultimate goal of becoming Kṛṣṇa conscious, without which everything is considered a failure.\"}]}],\"short_title\":\"Bg. 3.5\",\"medium_title\":\"Bhagavad-gītā As It Is 3.5\"},{\"id\":1005,\"meta\":{\"type\":\"books.Verse\",\"slug\":\"6\",\"show_in_menus\":false,\"seo_title\":\"\",\"search_description\":\"\",\"first_published_at\":null,\"alias_of\":null,\"locale\":\"en\"},\"title\":\"TEXT 6\",\"advanced_view_url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/3/advanced-view/#bb900\",\"language_menu\":[{\"display_name\":\"አማርኛ (Ethiopian)\",\"language_code\":\"am\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/am/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Български (Bulgarian)\",\"language_code\":\"bg\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/bg/library/bg/3/6/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Čeština (Czech)\",\"language_code\":\"cs\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/cs/library/bg/3/6/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Dansk (Danish)\",\"language_code\":\"da\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/da/library/bg/3/6/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Deutsch (German)\",\"language_code\":\"de\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/de/library/bg/3/6/\"},{\"display_name\":\"English\",\"language_code\":\"en\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/3/6/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Español (Spanish)\",\"language_code\":\"es\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/es/library/bg/3/6/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Eesti k