e\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":1028,\"bb\":919,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/3/9/b919/\",\"body_value\":\"Since one has to work even for the simple maintenance of the body, the prescribed duties for a particular social position and quality are so made that that purpose can be fulfilled. \u003cem\u003eYajña\u003c/em\u003e means Lord Viṣṇu, or sacrificial performances. All sacrificial performances also are meant for the satisfaction of Lord Viṣṇu. The \u003cem\u003eVedas\u003c/em\u003e enjoin: \u003cem\u003eyajño vai viṣṇuḥ.\u003c/em\u003e In other words, the same purpose is served whether one performs prescribed \u003cem\u003eyajñas\u003c/em\u003e or directly serves Lord Viṣṇu. Kṛṣṇa consciousness is therefore performance of \u003cem\u003eyajña\u003c/em\u003e as it is prescribed in this verse. The \u003cem\u003evarṇāśrama\u003c/em\u003e institution also aims at satisfying Lord Viṣṇu. \u003cem\u003eVarṇāśramācāravatā puruṣeṇa paraḥ pumān/ viṣṇur ārādhyate\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eViṣṇu Purāṇa\u003c/em\u003e 3.8.8).\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":1029,\"bb\":920,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/3/9/b920/\",\"body_value\":\"Therefore one has to work for the satisfaction of Viṣṇu. Any other work done in this material world will be a cause of bondage, for both good and evil work have their reactions, and any reaction binds the performer. Therefore, one has to work in Kṛṣṇa consciousness to satisfy Kṛṣṇa (or Viṣṇu); and while performing such activities one is in a liberated stage. This is the great art of doing work, and in the beginning this process requires very expert guidance. One should therefore act very diligently, under the expert guidance of a devotee of Lord Kṛṣṇa, or under the direct instruction of Lord Kṛṣṇa Himself (under whom Arjuna had the opportunity to work). Nothing should be performed for sense gratification, but everything should be done for the satisfaction of Kṛṣṇa. This practice will not only save one from the reaction of work, but also gradually elevate one to transcendental loving service of the Lord, which alone can raise one to the kingdom of God.\"}]}],\"short_title\":\"Bg. 3.9\",\"medium_title\":\"Bhagavad-gītā As It Is 3.9\"},{\"id\":1030,\"meta\":{\"type\":\"books.Verse\",\"slug\":\"10\",\"show_in_menus\":false,\"seo_title\":\"\",\"search_description\":\"\",\"first_published_at\":null,\"alias_of\":null,\"locale\":\"en\"},\"title\":\"TEXT 10\",\"advanced_view_url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/3/advanced-view/#bb921\",\"language_menu\":[{\"display_name\":\"አማርኛ (Ethiopian)\",\"language_code\":\"am\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/am/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Български (Bulgarian)\",\"language_code\":\"bg\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/bg/library/bg/3/10/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Čeština (Czech)\",\"language_code\":\"cs\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/cs/library/bg/3/10/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Dansk (Danish)\",\"language_code\":\"da\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/da/library/bg/3/10/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Deutsch (German)\",\"language_code\":\"de\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/de/library/bg/3/10/\"},{\"display_name\":\"English\",\"language_code\":\"en\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/3/10/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Español (Spanish)\",\"language_code\":\"es\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/es/library/bg/3/10/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Eesti keel (Estonian)\",\"language_code\":\"et\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/et/library/bg/3/10/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Suomen kieli (Finnish)\",\"language_code\":\"fi\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/fi/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Français (French)\",\"language_code\":\"fr\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/fr/library/bg/3/10/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Hrvatski (Croatian)\",\"language_code\":\"hr\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/hr/library/bg/3/10/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Magyar (Hungarian)\",\"language_code\":\"hu\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/hu/library/bg/3/10/\"},{\"display_name\":\"한국어 (