rial nature. Desire for overlording and for sense gratification is the greatest enemy of the conditioned soul; but by the strength of Kṛṣṇa consciousness, one can control the material senses, the mind and the intelligence. One may not give up work and prescribed duties all of a sudden; but by gradually developing Kṛṣṇa consciousness, one can be situated in a transcendental position without being influenced by the material senses and the mind – by steady intelligence directed toward one’s pure identity. This is the sum total of this chapter. In the immature stage of material existence, philosophical speculations and artificial attempts to control the senses by the so-called practice of yogic postures can never help a man toward spiritual life. He must be trained in Kṛṣṇa consciousness by higher intelligence.121:[\"$\",\"di"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"v\",\"1254-purport,1254-purport\",{\"className\":\"av-purport\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4\",\"children\":\"Purport\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L4a\",\"child-1259\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:42:child_items:4:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$13d\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L4a\",\"child-1260\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:42:child_items:4:children:1\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify italic\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"\u003cem\u003eThus end the Bhaktivedanta Purports to the Third Chapter of the\u003c/em\u003e Śrīmad Bhagavad-gītā \u003cem\u003ein the matter of\u003c/em\u003e Karma-yoga, \u003cem\u003eor the Discharge of One’s Prescribed Duty in Kṛṣṇa Consciousness.\u003c/em\u003e\"}}]}]]]}]\n13e:T41c,Vinod Bapat and Meenal Ba